# Cloudflare Pages _redirects supports path redirects only.
#
# Host/protocol canonicalization belongs in Cloudflare zone Redirect
# Rules / Bulk Redirects, not here:
#   - apex (toptier-electrical.com) → https://www.toptier-electrical.com
#     (308 Permanent Redirect, preserve path + query)
#   - http://* → https://* (Cloudflare's "Always Use HTTPS" toggle)
#
# Canonical host is `www.toptier-electrical.com`. Every sitemap entry,
# OG URL, and `<link rel="canonical">` already points there. Google's
# URL Inspection consistently selects www over apex due to external
# authority signals (GBP, citations, social), so we match that choice
# at the technical layer too.
#
# If apex starts returning 200 again without a redirect, expect Google
# Search Console to surface "Duplicate, Google chose different
# canonical than user" on apex URLs. The fix is to add the apex → www
# 308 rule above.

